LR284CA LR284CA
2026 2026
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE RESOLUTION 284CA
PROPOSED CONSTITUTIONAL AMENDMENT
Introduced by McKinney, 11.
Read first time January 07, 2026
Committee: Government, Military and Veterans Affairs
1 THE MEMBERS OF THE ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA, SECOND
2 SESSION, RESOLVE THAT:
3 Section 1. At the general election in November 2026, the following
4 proposed amendment to the Constitution of Nebraska shall be submitted to
5 the electors of the State of Nebraska for approval or rejection:
6 To amend Article VI, section 1:
7 VI-1 Every citizen of the United States who has attained the age of
8 sixteen eighteen years on or before the first Tuesday after the first
9 Monday in November and has resided within the state and the county and
10 voting precinct for the terms provided by law shall, except as provided
11 in section 2 of this article, be an elector for the calendar year in
12 which such citizen has attained the age of sixteen eighteen years and for
13 all succeeding calendar years.
14 Article VI, section 1, of the Constitution of Nebraska is repealed.
15 Sec. 2. The proposed amendment shall be submitted to the electors
16 in the manner prescribed by the Constitution of Nebraska, Article XVI,
17 section 1, with the following ballot language:
18 A constitutional amendment to permit persons who have attained the
19 age of sixteen years on or before the first Tuesday after the first
20 Monday in November to vote in the calendar year in which such persons
21 attain the age of sixteen years.
22 For
23 Against.
